https://seekingalpha.com/article/4385009-ozon-holdings-begins-u-s-ipo-effort ,
so between filing and actual IPO there is a time span of 20 days/14 business days (13 business days, if 11 November 2020/Veterans Day is excluded). From filing on 16 November 2020, 20 calendar days means the date would fall on Sun, 06 December 2020, the next trading day would be Mon, 07 Dec 2020.
14 business days means Tue, 08 Dec 2020 (if Thanksgiving and the Friday after are excluded)
13 business days means Mon, 07 Dec 2020. To satisfy the requirements of this question, ABNB must float on Thu, 03 December 2020 at the latest, which is three or four business days before the period that a medium sized Russian e-commerce platform is able to achieve. The calculus changes slightly, if one considers that Veterans Day is not a holiday with paid time off.
It appears difficult, but can be met, if
/no mandatory lock-up period is to be met and
/the investment banks which AirBnB picked as lead advisers (Morgan Stanley, GoldmanSachs) can make a difference with regards to speed and success of an IPO. I leave my forecast for the time being, checking Nasdaq's page regularly, until they post an estimated IPO (later than 03 Dec 2020).
